CatDescriptText: David Lee, shipper, Centre Avenue YMCA, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 7, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the Wacs and others women's units, with the exception of nurses, should be abolished in armed services during peacetime? Why?" answer reads: "I think that we should have them, but they shouldn't be up to full staff, to the number that we had during war time."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of David Lee wearing double breasted button overcoat, paisley scarf, moustache, and hat with band, standing on Wood Street with Dimlings candy store in background, Downtown
